      {
        "id": 2892422,
        "name": "Bob Hughes",
        "username": "Bob_Hughes",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/ed655f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-16T20:58:59.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A lot of my recent Chardonnay drinking has been focused on Oregon lately, so I decided to mix it up today and head back to France. Oh, and in case Brad pops in and asks, listening to Stan Getz &amp; Kenny Barron, The Complete People Time Recordings  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\" class=\"animated\"> .<br>\n<br>\n<br></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=565024&amp;iNote=8385531\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>1999 Domaine de la Bongran (Thevenet) M\u00e2con-Villages Cuv\u00e9e Tradition</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, M\u00e2connais, M\u00e2con-Villages (5/16/2020)</em><br>\nDark gold/bronze in the glass - the difference in color between this and the Bize and Lamy is pretty marked.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Tropical fruits on the nose here - pineapple? Either way, a great nose that you can savor at length.</p>\n<p>Rich and expansive on the palate - really spreads out and covers every nook &amp; cranny. I\u2019m getting towards the end of a case I bought on release, and this has been a pretty cool wine to track as it has evolved over the past two decades. The funny thing is, at 20 years of age this shows no signs of tiring either. Impressive wine.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2787618&amp;iNote=8385492\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2016 Hubert Lamy Saint-Aubin 1er Cru Derri\u00e8re Chez Edouard</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Saint-Aubin 1er Cru (5/16/2020)</em><br>\nVery focused nose, with a reductive note as well, but not as pronounced as the Bize.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Tart white fruit on an expansive palate - good acidity &amp; persistence. Another wine that is drinking very well today.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2984655&amp;iNote=8385479\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2016 Simon Bize Savigny-l\u00e8s-Beaune 1er Cru Aux Vergelesses</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Savigny-l\u00e8s-Beaune 1er Cru (5/16/2020)</em><br>\nReductive nose, like flint or petrol.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Expansive on the palate, decent acidity and good persistence on the finish. Very nice - this goes down dangerously easy.</p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
