        "id": 2892436,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-16T21:07:19.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m a big fan of Bongran with age. I drank a bottle of the 2000 during lockdown in France and it was a great way to make a virtual visit to the M\u00e2connais\u2014because that wine could come from nowhere else. The aging potential in a cold cellar is as long as almost anything made in Burgundy, and the \u201coff\u201d vintages tend to develop especially well. The oldest I have is a few bottles of the 1989, but a friend in the UK told me he has a 1964. Now that\u2019s a true unicorn!</p>",
