      {
        "id": 2892527,
        "name": "Kris_P@tten",
        "username": "Kris_Patten",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/kris_patten/{size}/2869_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-16T23:31:10.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Agreed William, when I started ITB we sold Martine\u2019s who repped Bongran in the US, and it was the most interesting white Burgundy I had tried, then over the years there would be botrytis years and lighter years but somehow they always had balance.</p>\n<p>It\u2019s one of the most unique wines produced in the world, produced by a very unique individual.  Still great value too.</p>",
